folder: Van Duzer Street & William Street, Staten Island, NY
original_title: Richmond: Van Duzer Street - William Street
text:
Van Duzer Street, at the S.E. corner of William Street, showing an old house and a one-story restaurant addition. The house appears on Beers's 1874 map; ownership is not indicated.

May 28, 1927

P. L. Sperr

folder: Van Duzer Street & William Street, Staten Island, NY
original_title: Richmond: Van Duzer Street - William Street
text:
292 Van Duzer Street, at the S.W. corner of William Street (right), showing the home of the Democratic Club. The house was owned by Dr. W. C. Anderson in 1874; by Karl Kapff from 1898 to 1907, and by A. Sommers in 1917. Dates refer to maps on which the owners' names appear.

May 25, 1935

P. L. Sperr
